---
title: Tilapia with Scallion Sriracha Pesto over Ginger Rice with Green Beans
description: Classic basil pesto never goes out of style, but tonight’s scallion pesto is just the fun, dynamic condiment we’ve been craving. The scallions are finely chopped, then mixed with sesame oil and seeds, ginger, sugar, lemon juice, and Sriracha. The result? A tangy, sweet, savory, and spicy flavor explosion that provides just the right contrast to mild tilapia fillets, fluffy ginger rice, and snappy green beans.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/tilapia-with-scallion-sriracha-pesto-63f87575.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/tilapia-with-scallion-sriracha-pesto-61e6fcf13ff433653e70d704-2e9f4751.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tilapia-with-scallion-sriracha-pesto-61e6fcf13ff433653e70d704
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Asian
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 59 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1090 mg
---

Wash and dry produce (except green beans). Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and finely chop @scallions{4}. Halve @lemon{1}; cut one half into wedges (for 4 servings, halve one lemon and quarter remaining).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add 1 TBSP ginger (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4) and a @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}. Cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine scallions, @sesame oil{1%tbsp}, half the @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @ginger{1%tsp}, @sugar{1%tsp}, juice from lemon half, and @Sriracha{1%tsp} to taste. (For 4 servings, use all sesame seeds, 2 TBSP olive oil, 2 tsp ginger, 2 tsp sugar, and juice from both lemon halves.) Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; add more ginger or lemon juice to taste.

Pat @tilapia{11%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add tilapia and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat.

While tilapia cooks, pierce green bean bag with a fork; place bag on a #plate. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> No microwave? No problem! Steam green beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Transfer @green beans{6%oz} to a second medium bowl; add @butter{1%tbsp}. Toss until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice and green beans between plates. Arrange tilapia over rice; drizzle with scallion Sriracha pesto and @soy sauce{2%tbsp} to taste. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.